tabernacles of Roman churches; gilded silver, both secular and ecclesiastical; elaborately embossed display dishes; and the production of medals. Concentrating on selected pieces by such master sculptors as Bernini and leading metal-workers such as Giovanni Giardini, Montagu examines the often tortuous relationship between patrons and artists and elucidates the relationship between those who provided the drawings or models and the craftsmen who executed the finished sculptures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 7aART / History / General.2bisacsh  aAlgardi, Alessandro:.  aAquaviva, Cardinal:.  aBaltimore, Walter’s Art Gallery, A. Algardi, Putto on a Hippocamp:.  aBarberini, Cardinal Francesco senior:.  aBarberini, family:.  aBernini, Gianlorenzo:.  aBronze Statuettes (Anonymous), Busts of the Twelve Caesars:.  aChristie’s, after Bernini, St Catherine:.  aColonna, Filippo, Conestabile:.  aCorsini, Cardinal Neri:.  aCorsini, family:.  aFerrata, Ercole:.  aFoggini, Giovanni Battista, Boreas Raping Orithyia:.  aGiambologna:.  aGirardon, François:.  aGiustiniani, Vincenzo:.  aHenrietta Maria (Queen of England):.  aInnocent X, Pope:.  aLigari, Pietro, drawing after Algardi:.  aLorenzani, Giovanni Andrea:.  aLos Angeles, County Museum of Art, A. Montauti, Triumph of Neptune/Rape of Europa:.  aLouis XIV (of France):.  aLudovisi, family:.  aMontauti, Antonio:.  aMoretti, Antonio Amice:.  aPalazzo Corsini, bronzes:.  aSannesi, Francesco:.  aSoldani, Massimiliano:.  aSta Maria della Concezione, G. Lanfranco, Immacolata:.  aUrban VIII, Pope:.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertThe A. W. Mellon Lectures in the Fine Arts eBook Packagez978311129290840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691252797?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691252797423Cov